 Woodrow Wilson and the British government to recognize a Jewish homeland in Palestine. Combining narrative biography with a passionate argument for why Brandeis matters today, Rosen explores what Brandeis, the Jeffersonian prophet, can teach us about historic and contemporary questions involving the Constitution, monopoly, corporate and federal power, technology, privacy, free speech, and Zionism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aJewish judgeszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aJudgeszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Lawyers & Judges.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2016z978311066771440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300160444423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300160444.jpg  a978-3-11-066771-4  YUP eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles